An Igbosere Magistrates’ Court in Lagos State yesterday remanded a nursing mother, Olufunmilola Adisa, suspected of killing her baby, at the Lagos State University Teaching Hospital (LASUTH) for psychiatric evaluation. Adisa, 22, is accused by the police of drowning her 21 months old child in a bucket of water. She is receiving free legal representation from the Office of the Public Defender (OPD). The evaluation would enable medical authorities determine the state of her mental health.
 
Delivering her ruling, the presiding magistrate, Mrs. Dora Ojo, granted the application of the OPD representing the defendant that based on Section 217 (3) of Lagos Administration of the Criminal of Justice law of 2015, the defendant should be sent and remanded at the teaching hospital for necessary psychiatric test in order to determine her state of mental health.  To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .